  <span id="freeText14456553934595833138" style="display:none">Gave up on this book after about 200 pages. Would have loved to read more if I could stand the writing -- at its best, it is a powerful exploration of the moral ambiguities surrounding the West's role in the Sudan. But the message gets bogged down in trite, heavy-handed dialogue and tired platitudes, and after a while I just couldn't stand any more.</span>
